  <li><strong>National trend:</strong> More cities requiring STR permits (Penang, KL already have systems)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Our recommendation:</strong> Stay compliant NOW. Future regulations likely grandfather in existing operators who've been following rules.</p>

<h2>What If You're Currently Operating "Under the Radar"?</h2>

<p>We get calls from owners in buildings with explicit bans, asking us to manage anyway. Our answer: NO.</p>

<p>Here's why:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Fines:</strong> RM500-2,000 per incident (accumulates fast)</li>
  <li><strong>Legal action:</strong> JMB/MC can sue for injunction + damages</li>
  <li><strong>Platform risk:</strong> Airbnb may delist if building management complains</li>
  <li><strong>iHousing reputation:</strong> We won't risk our business relationship with management bodies</li>
